lct - Local configuration tool

Usage:
  lct COMMAND
  lct [COMMAND] --help | -h
  lct --version | -v

Commands:
  init          Initialize lct configuration
  bootstrap     Bootstrap your local configuration
  gather        Gather local configuration files (flags possible secrets before committing)
  install       Install modules from an LCTFile or globally (bin links are created only for high-confidence scripts)
  self-update   Update lct to the latest release
  remove        Remove modules from an LCTFile or globally
  alias         Manage lct aliases
  dotfiles      Manage dotfiles list
  configs       Manage configs list
  env           Manage local environment variables
  reload        Reload lct environment variables and aliases into the current shell
  plugin        Develop and manage lct plugins
  completions   Generate bash completions
  config        Open your config files in your nvim
  setup         Setup lct in your shell
  prune         Prune config and plugins files

Options:
  --help, -h
    Show this help

  --version, -v
    Show version number

Environment Variables:
  SOFTWARE_DIR
    Base directory for downloaded libraries managed on this machine.
    Default: ~/software

  CONFIG_DIR
    Base directory for local configuration files.
    Default: ~/.config

  SHARE_DIR
    Base directory for local shared application data.
    Default: ~/.local/share

  STATE_DIR
    Base directory for persistent local state data.
    Default: ~/.local/state

  CACHE_DIR
    Base directory for local cache data.
    Default: ~/.cache
